.\" Man page for serenium
.TH SERENIUM 1 "2024-01-01" "Serenium 1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
serenium \- A production-ready package builder for creating Debian packages
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B serenium
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]...
.SH DESCRIPTION
Serenium is a production-ready tool to scaffold new packages with proper Debian packaging structure. It provides an intuitive interface for creating both regular packages and metapackages with comprehensive validation, configuration file support, and beautiful terminal themes.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-help\fR, \fB\-h\fR
Show help message and exit.
.TP
\fB\-\-version\fR, \fB\-v\fR
Show version information and exit.
.TP
\fB\-\-config\fR=\fIFILE\fR, \fB\-c\fR \fIFILE\fR
Load configuration from YAML or JSON file.
.TP
\fB\-\-theme\fR=\fITHEME\fR, \fB\-t\fR \fITHEME\fR
Select terminal theme. Available themes: serenium, cyberpunk, ocean, forest, sunset, monochrome, neon, matrix.
.TP
\fB\-\-create-sample-config\fR
Create a sample configuration file and exit.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Interactive mode
.B serenium
.TP
Use configuration file
.B serenium \-\-config my-package.yaml
.TP
Specify theme
.B serenium \-\-theme ocean
.TP
Create sample configuration
.B serenium \-\-create-sample-config
.SH CONFIGURATION FILES
Serenium supports both YAML and JSON configuration files for automated package creation. A sample configuration file can be generated using the \fB\-\-create-sample-config\fR option.
.PP
Example YAML configuration:
.nf
.RS
name: my-package
version: 1.0.0
description: My awesome package
is_metapackage: false
dependencies:
  - python3
  - python3-yaml
maintainer: Your Name
email: your.email@example.com
.RE
.fi
