.SH PACKAGE TYPES
.TP
Regular packages
Include actual files and scripts, can have desktop entries, appear in application menus, and include launcher scripts for tools.
.TP
Metapackages
Only install dependencies, no files included (except Debian packaging), useful for creating tool collections, and have smaller package size.
.SH VALIDATION
Serenium includes comprehensive validation:
.RS
.IP \[bu] 2
Package Name Validation: Ensures names follow Debian standards
.IP \[bu] 2
Version Validation: Semantic versioning format checking
.IP \[bu] 2
Email Validation: Basic email format verification
.IP \[bu] 2
Input Sanitization: Removes potentially dangerous characters
.IP \[bu] 2
File Permission Checks: Ensures executable files have correct permissions
.IP \[bu] 2
Dependency Validation: Warns about potential issues
.RE
.SH LOGGING
Serenium provides detailed logging for debugging. Logs are written to \fBserenium.log\fR in the current directory.
